{"title_page": "Aleksandar Kosti\u0107", "text_new": "{{Infobox football biography\n| name        = Aleksandar Kosti\u0107\n| fullname    = \n| image       = \n| birth_date  = {{birth date and age|df=yes|1995|10|12}}\n| birth_place = [[Vienna]], [[Austria]]\n| height      = {{Height|m=1.66}}\n| position    = [[Midfielder]]\n| currentclub = [[FC Blau-Wei\u00df Linz|Blau-Wei\u00df Linz]]\n| clubnumber  = 17\n| youthyears1 = 2001\u20132010\n| youthclubs1 = [[SK Rapid Wien|Rapid Wien]]\n| youthyears2 = 2010\u20132011\n| youthclubs2 = Slovan HAC\n| youthyears3 = 2011\u20132013\n| youthclubs3 = [[Wiener Sport-Club]]\n| years1      = 2013\u20132015  | clubs1 = [[Wiener Sport-Club]]                  | caps1 = 61  | goals1 = 9\n| years2      = 2015\u20132017  | clubs2 = [[First Vienna FC|First Vienna]]       | caps2 = 42  | goals2 = 5\n| years3      = 2017\u20132018  | clubs3 = [[SK Rapid Wien|Rapid Wien]]           | caps3 = 6   | goals3 = 0\n| years4      = 2017\u20132018  | clubs4 = \u2192 [[SK Rapid Wien|Rapid Wien II]]      | caps4 = 26  | goals4 = 8\n| years5      = 2019       | clubs5 = [[FK Radni\u010dki Ni\u0161|Radni\u010dki Ni\u0161]]       | caps5 = 0   | goals5 = 0\n| years6      = 2019\u2013      | clubs6 = [[FC Blau-Wei\u00df Linz|Blau-Wei\u00df Linz]]   | caps6 = 17  | goals6 = 2\n| pcupdate    = 11 April 2020\n}}\n'''Aleksandar Kosti\u0107''' (born 12 October 1995) is an Austrian footballer who plays for [[FC Blau-Wei\u00df Linz]] .<ref name=\"soccerway\">{{soccerway|aleksandar-kostic/292311}}</ref>\n\n==Career==\n===Early career===\nKostic debuted as senior in 2012 playing with [[Wiener Sport-Club]] in the Regionalliga where he stayed until 2015 when he moved to same level side [[First Vienna FC]] where he played two seasons.<ref name=\"soccerway\"/>\n\n===Rapid Wien===\nOver a 100 appearances in Regionalliga in 5 seasons called the atention of Austrian giants [[SK Rapid Wien]] which brought him back in summer 2017. Rapid was a club where he spent much of his youth career, between 2001 and 2010. Rapid\u00b4s academy product, Kostic was this time joining the main team and made hid debut with one appearances in the [[2017\u201318 Austrian Football Bundesliga]], plus 5 in the first half of the [[2018\u201319 Austrian Football Bundesliga]]. Simultaneously, he also played with the second team in the Regionalliga where he was much more active making 26 appearances and scoring 8 goals in that same period.<ref name=\"soccerway\"/>\n\n===Radni\u010dki Ni\u0161===\nDespite receving much more playing time in his second year in Rapid, both in main and second team, during winter-break of 2018\u201319 season Kostic moved abroad to his ancestors country, Serbia, and signed with top-level side [[FK Radni\u010dki Ni\u0161]]. However, his move didn\u00b4t went as expected, club\u00b4s coach gave preference to other options, and, after ending the season without even debuting in the [[Serbian SuperLiga]], he departed and returned to Austria.<ref name=\"soccerway\"/>\n\n===Blau-Wei\u00df Linz===\nOn 14 June 2019 [[FC Blau-Wei\u00df Linz]] confirmed, that Kosti\u0107 had joined the club on a one-year deal.<ref>[https://www.blauweiss-linz.at/news/2686/neuzugang--aleksandar-kostic/ Neuzugang: Aleksandar Kostic], blauweiss-linz.at, 14 June 2019</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|30em}}\n\n==External links==\n*[https://www.oefb.at/Spieler/234421/?Aleksandar-Kostic Aleksandar Kosti\u0107] at \u00d6FB\n*{{WorldFootball.net|aleksandar-kostic}}\n\n{{FC Blau-Wei\u00df Linz squad}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Kosti\u0107, Aleksandar}}\n[[Category:Austrian footballers]]\n[[Category:Sportspeople from Vienna]]\n[[Category:Austrian people of Serbian descent]]\n[[Category:1995 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:SK Rapid Wien players]]\n[[Category:Wiener Sport-Club players]]\n[[Category:First Vienna FC players]]\n[[Category:FK Radni\u010dki Ni\u0161 players]]\n[[Category:FC Blau-Wei\u00df Linz players]]\n[[Category:Austrian Football Bundesliga players]